The house of the Ogun State Commissioner for Agriculture, Dr Samson Odedina, was razed by fire on Thursday. The house which is located at Kemta Idi-Aba Area of Abeokuta caught fire during the day and burnt down, but the cause of the fire could not be ascertained as at the time of filing this report. Dr Odedina who confirmed the incident, appreciated God that no life was lost in the incident. He said he was at work when he was alerted of the fire and that before he arrived his neighbors and motorcyclists were able to evacuate his cars from the compound. Director of the Ogun State Fire Service, Fatai Adefala, said the fire could be traced to the kitchen. 